         <head xml:lang="en"/>         
         <div type="commentary" subtype="frontmatter" xml:space="preserve"><p>Medical prescriptions. Papyrus sheet (10.6 x 7.5 cm) fairly regularly cut off on all sides, except for the left margin, which is partly damaged. The <emph rend="italics">verso</emph> preserves a recipe for the preparation of a tooth powder (see Orib., <emph rend="italics">Syn</emph>., 3.172 [CMG 6.3, 109.8-10 Raed.], 178 [CMG 6.3, 109.6-8 Raed.], 5.25 [CMG 6.3, 163.12-9 Raed.]); on the <emph rend="italics">recto</emph>, a documentary text from Hermoupolis (= SB 16.12244). The script is a documentary hand assignable to the 4th cent. AD.</p></div>         <div xml:lang="grc" type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><ab><lb n="1" xml:id="lb1"/><expan>ξηρ<ex>ίον</ex></expan> <expan>ὀδό<unclear>ντ</unclear><ex>ων</ex></expan> <expan>λευκ<ex>ῶν</ex></expan> καὶ <expan>ἀβρώτ<ex>ων</ex></expan>•<lb n="2"/>ἁλὸς <expan>ἀ<unclear>μμω</unclear>νιακ<ex>οῦ</ex></expan> <expan><ex>δραχμὴ</ex></expan> <num value="1">α</num><lb n="3"/><expan>γληχῶν<ex>ος</ex></expan> <expan><ex>δραχμαὶ</ex></expan> <num value="2">β</num><lb n="4"/>ἴρεως <expan><ex>δραχμὴ</ex></expan> <num value="1">α</num><lb n="5"/><expan>πεπέρε<ex>ως</ex></expan> <expan>κόκκου<ex>ς</ex></expan> <num value="20"><hi rend="supraline">κ</hi></num></ab></div>         <div type="commentary" subtype="linebyline">            <list>               <item corresp="#lb1" xml:space="preserve"><ref>1</ref> <p>This is the first attestation of the word ἄβρωτος on papyrus. "Contraraiment à H.-S. [= <listBibl><bibl><ref target="http://papyri.info/biblio/9672">Harrauer-Sijpesteijn 1981</ref></bibl></listBibl>= MPER 13.7] et à D.R. Jordan [= <listBibl><bibl><ref target="http://papyri.info/biblio/28853">Jordan 1982</ref></bibl></listBibl>], nous estimons que l'adj. ἄβρωτος ne signifie pas 'non attaqué par une carie', ma qu'il decrit l'effet non abrasif de la poudre sur les dents (comparer la recette de Galien, <emph rend="italics">Comp.med.sec.loc.</emph> 5.4 [12, 889.7-9 K])" (<listBibl><bibl><ref target="http://papyri.info/biblio/28856">Marganne 1983</ref></bibl></listBibl>, 250).</p></item>            </list>         </div>
